Healthcare Insurance Cost Explorer
==================================

An interactive data dashboard built with Python, Pandas, and Streamlit, designed to visualize and analyze how factors like age, BMI, smoking status, and region influence insurance charges.

FEATURES
--------
- Load and explore healthcare insurance data of 1300+ policyholders
- Filter views by region, smoking status, gender, and more
- Interactive charts built using Plotly (click on points to view exact values)
- Hover, zoom, and filter features to assist exploration
- Key findings surfaced through correlation and statistical analysis

TECH STACK
----------
Python         : Data processing & backend  
Pandas / NumPy : Data cleaning and analysis  
Plotly         : Interactive visualizations  
Streamlit      : Web-based dashboard  
GitHub         : Version control & hosting  
Excel          : Initial data formatting

KEY INSIGHTS
------------
- Smoking is the strongest driver of high insurance costs (300%+ increase in average charge).
- BMI above 30 is associated with higher-than-average charges, especially among smokers.
- Age and number of children have moderate influence.
- Region shows minimal impact, but slight variations exist in the southeast.

HOW TO RUN LOCALLY
------------------
1. Clone the repository:

   git clone https://github.com/yourusername/healthcare-insurance-dashboard.git  
   cd healthcare-insurance-dashboard

2. Install the requirements:

   pip install -r requirements.txt

3. Run the app:

   streamlit run app.py

PROJECT STRUCTURE
-----------------
app.py               - Main Streamlit app  
insurance.csv        - Dataset (from Kaggle or local file)  
requirements.txt     - Python dependencies  
README.txt           - Project overview

DATASET
-------
Source: Kaggle - Medical Cost Personal Datasets  
Contains demographic and medical info for over 1,300 individuals:  
- age, sex, bmi, children, smoker, region, charges

STATUS
------
Completed and deployed on Streamlit Cloud  
Future enhancements planned (e.g., model predictions, more filters)

